description:
This is my second quest after Hyrule in Chaos & I spent almost 2 years on it. It’s one amazing quest which has an oriental feel to it and will leave players impressed with its uniqueness and originality.

Please use the 183 player to play the quest & use the SFX dat file which I compiled strange sounds. You can visit An Quan Town after Lvl 1 is completed, which is located along the Taoland beach. I also enabled the overworld map for the benefit of players playing a newer beta.

Features of the Quest :
- 2 complete ( 12 x 8 ) overworlds called Orient & Taoland; 
- 2 small towns called Ping An Town & An Quan Town; 
- 9 dungeons with multi-floors/multi-entrances;
- 5 elemental shrines with powerful element items;
- Superbly nice music, most of which are Chinese pop songs;
- Chinese characters representing the elemental shrines;
- Tons of secrets to explore & find;
- Pure Tileset with 2 new dungeon palettes;
- 24 Heart Containers with 36 HC Pieces to get.

This is a revamp of my second quest The Tao Of Link. I changed the music, mixed up key item placements in dungeons & shrines, as well as added two new items.

Features of the Quest :
- 2 complete ( 12 x 8 ) overworlds called Orient & Taoland; 
- 2 small towns called Ping An Town & An Quan Town; 
- 9 dungeons with multi-floors/multi-entrances;
- 5 elemental shrines with powerful element items;
- New oriental music, most of which are Chinese pop songs;
- Chinese characters representing the elemental shrines;
- Tons of secrets to explore & find;
- Pure Tileset with 2 new dungeon palettes;
- Weather has improved in Orient & Taoland;
- Addition of Farore’s Wind in Orient & Nayru’s Love in Taoland.
